      "medicine": "lisinopril",
      "allergy": "ace_inhibitors",
      "reason": "Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor. A stated allergy to 'ace_inhibitors' means that administering lisinopril would directly conflict with this allergy. Allergic reactions to ACE inhibitors can range from skin rashes to severe, potentially life-threatening angioedema (swelling of the face, lips, tongue, or throat) and anaphylaxis.",
      "severity": "HIGH"
    }
  ],
  "risk_level": "HIGH",
  "analysis_summary": "There are significant clinical concerns including a high-severity drug-drug interaction between ibuprofen and lisinopril, increasing the risk of acute kidney injury and reduced blood pressure control. Additionally, lisinopril directly conflicts with the patient's stated 'ace_inhibitors' allergy, posing a high risk for severe allergic reactions such as angioedema."
}
</json>
